Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on embedding cryptographic properties in Compressive Sampling (CS) and proposes a bi-level protection (BLP) model for constructing secure compressive sampling scheme. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the encoding and decoding process in CS and proposes techniques to establish secret key-related sparsifying basis. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper applies the proposed model to construct digital image cipher under the parallel compressive sampling reconstruction framework. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the properties of the proposed cipher, such as compressibility and robustness, which are relevant to computer vision and pattern recognition applications. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although less likely, the paper may also belong to this sub-category as it discusses the security of a networked system (compressive sampling scheme) and its resilience to various attack scenarios.
